opular methods in the field. The\nproposed fFRI is able to predict B-factors for alpha-carbons of the HIV virus\ncapsid (313,236 residues) in less than 30 seconds on a single processor using\nonly one core. Finally, we demonstrate the application of FRI and aFRI to\nprotein domain analysis.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 8 Dec 2014 21:46:23 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-12-10"}
